        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Meanwhile, for the most urgent use-cases, we have provided some `on_foo` callbacks such as [on_list](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/af707dd24261f34a72ba7bbea5cf2e802f81837d/runtime/doc/lsp.txt#L1332) and [on_jump](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/af707dd24261f34a72ba7bbea5cf2e802f81837d/runtime/doc/diagnostic.txt#L191) , so that users can do arbitrary things before/after an action occurs. That's a stop-gap until the generalized \"promise\" interface is achieved.\n\nI understand that `on_list` can be used to do arbitrary stuff. The problem I want to raise is it is easy to override the handler completely, but it is difficult to make small augmentations to the default handler because the default handler isn't exposed.\nI think the default handler is really nice and covers 99% of all common use cases. It just lacks the ability to override the buffer opening behaviour. If either a new flag is added or the default handler exposed, we can cover 99% of use cases without requiring the user to basically copy paste the source code of the default handler.",
