        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> ### Option 2\n> Allow the default on_list handler to be exposed as `vim.lsp.buf.on_list`.\n\nThis is possible. One reason I use `switchbuf` is because of the `on-list` behavior in `vim.lsp.buf`. Only the implementation of `vim.lsp.buf.references` is inconsistent with the others, as it always creates a quickfix list. I can finish refactoring this part first and then follow up to see if such a change is appropriate.\n",
