        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Revisiting the current `on_list` interface, I think it's a bit awkward... Since we set the qflist context, we don't actually need to pass an `on_list` to functions like `lsp.buf.definition` to achieve its functionality; we can do the same thing just by using `getqflist(context)`, then call whatever users want. Perhaps what we really need is a callback that triggers after `lsp.buf.definition` is called, so that we can:\n1. Implement the existing functionality of jumping directly when there is only one item.\n2. Implement the callback mentioned in this issue that triggers after `definition`, allowing us to restore `switchbuf`.",
